msgid "Assistive Technologies"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: abstract/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:11
msgid ""
"The GNOME desktop includes assistive technologies to support users with "
"various impairments and special needs, and to interact with common assistive "
"devices. This chapter describes several assistive technology applications "
"designed to meet the needs of users with physical disabilities like low "
"vision or impaired motor skills."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: sect1/title
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:25
msgid "Enabling Assistive Technologies"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: sect1/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:27
msgid ""
"To configure accessibility features, open the respective settings dialog by "
"right-clicking the desktop and choosing <guimenu>Settings</guimenu> and then "
"<guimenu>Universal Access</guimenu>. Each assistive feature can be enabled "
"separately using this dialog."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: sect1/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:34
msgid ""
"If you need a more direct access to individual assistive features, turn on "
"<guimenu>Always Show Universal Access Menu</guimenu> in the "
"<guimenu>Universal Access</guimenu> dialog. A new menu will appear on the "
"bottom panel."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: sect1/title
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:42
msgid "Visual Assistance"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: sect1/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:44
msgid ""
"In the <guimenu>Seeing</guimenu> section of the <guimenu>Universal Access</"
"guimenu> dialog, you can enable features that help people with impaired "
"vision."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:52
msgid ""
"Turning on <guimenu>High Contrast</guimenu> enables high contrast black and "
"white icons in the GNOME desktop."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:58
msgid ""
"Turning on <guimenu>Large Text</guimenu> enlarges the font used in the user "
"interface."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:64
msgid ""
"Turning on <guimenu>Zoom</guimenu> enables a screen magnifier. You can set "
"the desired magnification and magnifier behavior, including color effects."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:70
msgid ""
"By customizing the <guimenu>Cursor Size</guimenu> you can increase the "
"visibility of the mouse cursor."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:76
msgid ""
"If the <guimenu>Screen Reader</guimenu> is turned on, any UI element or text "
"that receives keyboard focus is read aloud."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:82
msgid ""
"If the <guimenu>Sound Keys</guimenu> are turned on, a sound is played "
"whenever <keycap>Num Lock</keycap> or <keycap>Caps Lock</keycap> are turned "
"on."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: sect1/title
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:91
msgid "Hearing Assistance"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: sect1/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:93
msgid ""
"In the <guimenu>Hearing</guimenu> section of the <guimenu>Universal Access</"
"guimenu> dialog, you can enable features helping people with impaired "
"hearing."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: sect1/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:99
msgid ""
"If the <guimenu>Visual Alerts</guimenu> are turned on, a window title or the "
"entire screen is flashed when an alert sound occurs for the respective "
"application."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: sect1/title
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:106
msgid "Keyboard and Mouse"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: sect1/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:108
msgid ""
"In the <guimenu>Typing</guimenu> and <guimenu>Pointing and Clicking</"
"guimenu> sections of the <guimenu>Universal Access</guimenu> dialog, you can "
"enable features that help people with mobility impairments."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:116
msgid ""
"If the <guimenu>Screen Keyboard</guimenu> is turned on, a virtual keyboard "
"appears whenever you need to enter text. You can use the screen keyboard by "
"clicking the virtual keys."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:123
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Repeat Keys</guimenu> lets you configure if and when a key is "
"repeated when it is pressed for a longer time. You can either turn this "
"feature <guimenu>Off</guimenu> or configure a <guimenu>Delay</guimenu> and "
"the <guimenu>Speed</guimenu> by which keys are repeated."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:131
msgid ""
"Under <guimenu>Cursor Blinking</guimenu> you can configure if and at which "
"speed the cursor blinks in text fields (for example in a terminal)."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:137
msgid ""
"Click <guimenu>Typing Assist (AccessX)</guimenu> to open a dialog where you "
"can enable various features that make typing easier:"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:143
msgid ""
"With <guimenu>Enable by Keyboard</guimenu>, you can turn accessibility "
"features on or off by using the keyboard."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:149
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Sticky Keys</guimenu> allows you to type key combinations one key "
"at a time rather than having to hold down all of the keys at once. For "
"example, the <keycombo> <keycap function=\"alt\"/><keycap function=\"tab\"/"
"></keycombo> shortcut switches between windows."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:156
msgid ""
"With sticky keys turned off, you need to hold down both keys at the same "
"time. With sticky keys turned on, press <keycap function=\"alt\"/> and then "
"<keycap function=\"tab\"/> to do the same."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:163
msgid ""
"Turn on <guimenu>Slow Keys</guimenu> if you want a delay between pressing a "
"key and the letter being displayed on the screen. This means that you need "
"to hold down each key you want to type for a little while before it appears. "
"Use slow keys if you accidentally press several keys at a time when you "
"type, or if you find it difficult to press the right key on the keyboard "
"first time."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:173
msgid ""
"Turn on <guimenu>Bounce Keys</guimenu> to ignore key presses that are "
"rapidly repeated. This can help, for example, if you have hand tremors which "
"cause you to press a key multiple times when you only want to press it once."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:183
msgid ""
"Turn on <guimenu>Mouse Keys</guimenu> to control the mouse pointer using the "
"numeric keypad on your keyboard."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:189
msgid ""
"Click <guimenu>Click Assist</guimenu> to open a dialog where you can enable "
"various features that make clicking easier: simulated secondary click and "
"hover click."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:196
msgid ""
"Turn on <guimenu>Simulated Secondary Click</guimenu> to activate the "
"secondary click (usually the right mouse button) by holding down the primary "
"button for a predefined <guimenu>Acceptance delay</guimenu>. This is useful "
"if you find it difficult to move your fingers individually on one hand, or "
"if your pointing device only has a single button."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:206
msgid ""
"Turn on <guimenu>Hover Click</guimenu> to trigger a click by hovering your "
"mouse pointer over an object on the screen. This is useful if you find it "
"difficult to move the mouse and click at the same time. If this feature is "
"turned on, a small Hover Click window opens and stays above all of your "
"other windows. You can use this to choose what sort of click should happen "
"when you hover. When you hover your mouse pointer over a button and do not "
"move it, the pointer gradually changes color. When it has fully changed "
"color, the button will be clicked."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: listitem/para
#: xml/gnome_accessibility.xml:220
msgid ""
"Use the slider to adjust the <guimenu>Double-Click Delay</guimenu> according "
"to your needs."
msgstr ""

